    "narrative": "The Ghost Ride the WHIP lineup is headlined by **Corbin Carroll**, who boasts a commanding 87.14 score against Kremer. His elite projection is buoyed by a +16% park adjustment and a prime spot in the #2 hole, making him our primary engine for SB and run production today. Joining him in the \"Strong\" start tier are **Jose Caballero** (70.88) and **Giancarlo Stanton** (68.24), both of whom benefit significantly from favorable wind conditions and a soft matchup against Kikuchi. **Jose Caballero** represents our highest-upside play for steals, as his 13% platoon boost against the lefty makes him a near-essential start despite the #8 spot in the order.\n\nThe most difficult decision for the optimizer involved **Max Muncy**, who fell just short of the active roster with a 43.60 score. While he benefits from a +10% park factor, the matchup against Nathan Eovaldi\u2014an elite arm with a 3.17 xERA\u2014proved too daunting to warrant a start over the high-ceiling profiles of **Tyler Soderstrom** or **Austin Riley**. Risk remains a factor with our pending lineups; **Dalton Rushing**, **Alex Freeland**, and **Tyler Soderstrom** are currently slotted based on historical assumptions, and any downward shift in their batting order could necessitate a re-evaluation of our efficiency targets. Furthermore, while **James Wood** is in the lineup, managers should be wary of his matchup against Skenes; the elite catcher's pop time is a specific deterrent for our SB-heavy strategy today. Finally, note that **Vinnie Pasquantino**, **Mickey Moniak**, and **Brice Turang** are unavailable for selection due to team off-days, further condensing our options for the daily rotation.",
